The paper deals with the robustness of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves modifying the architecture of CNNs, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of CNNs to adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to improve the defense ability of CNNs, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
